-- P2a: move body/hand/foot skincare rows to bath_body (face-only skincare model).
--
-- Context (2026-06-29): skincare is being narrowed to FACE ONLY. The detector-
-- driven bath_body backfill (20260629140000) already moved the 4,084 rows whose
-- product-type form the personal-care detector claims (Bath & Shower, Body
-- Moisturiser, Body Scrub, Body Oil, Shaving, Deodorant, Hand Care). This P2a
-- migration moves the COMPLEMENT: skincare rows the categoriser's subcategory
-- tagger labelled body / hand / foot but whose product-type form the detector
-- does NOT claim (body SPF/Mist/Serum/Cleanser/Mask, foot care, hand care types,
-- generic 'Skincare'). The detector deliberately defers SPF to skincare and has
-- no foot arm, so these are its blind spot.
--
-- Scope: top_category='skincare' AND subcategory IN ('body','hand','foot'),
-- excluding subcategory='both' (held for P2b per-row face/body review) and
-- excluding cleanup_remove rows. Frozen to explicit ids from a reviewed dry-run
-- (live state 2026-06-29): 2,078 rows — body 1,810 / hand 147 / foot 121.
--
-- Transform (user ruling 2026-06-29): a PURE move.
--   top_category -> 'bath_body'; tags -> ['bath_body', subcategory];
--   subcategory PRESERVED; product_type UNTOUCHED (accept the cosmetic
--   bath_body/body vocab mix vs the detector's 'Body Moisturiser' etc.;
--   optional to normalise later, not now).
--
-- Safety:
--   * every UPDATE guarded by top_category='skincare' AND subcategory=<the
--     bucket> -> a row since recategorised is skipped, not clobbered;
--   * explicit ids only (no name predicate) — exactly the reviewed set;
--   * disjoint from the P1 cleanup (0 overlap with its 121 exclude ids) and from
--     the detector backfill (those rows are already bath_body, not skincare);
--   * subcategory='both' (231) and all face skincare are untouched.
--
-- Idempotent: re-running no-ops once top_category<>'skincare'. Transactional.
--
-- FOLLOW-UP (queued, not in this migration): the live bath_body detector does
-- not claim body-SPF/Mist/Serum/foot-care forms, so new imports keep landing
-- them in skincare/body. A paired categoriser PR must widen the detector so
-- skincare stays face-only durably.

begin;

